First question; do you tend to see better drops in the halls of testing (skyshrine armor), or in the wing(s) that drop the pieces for the Kael armor?<br>
---<br>
<br>
The drop rates really are random, I've seen 6 drops in 7 kills from drakes, and I've seen no drops on 10-15+ drakes/wurms in a row.  I can't say anything about SS armor for sure, but I'm almost positive the drop rates are similiar.  BTW -- Kael quest pieces drop in the west wing of ToV, the 4 way (area between the wings), and off a FEW CoV faction mobs in north wing pretty deep in.  <br>
<br>
---<br>
Second question; are you seeing a disparity between the drops? Chiefly a lot of plate drops, mediocre leather and silk drops, and horrible chain drops?<br>
---<br>
<br>
I would say from personal experience, leather is the most common, followed closely by silk.  Before the plate drop rate increase patch, it was rarer than chain.  Now, it is considerably more common than chain.  To summarize, in order of rarity starting from greatest: Chain, plate, silk, leather.  I don't have any facts to back this up, just speaking from my personal experience from mobs in west wing and 4 way. <br>
<br>
